  20 Jul 2004; Tom Gall <tgall@gentoo.org> xv-3.10a-r6.ebuild:
  stable on ppc64, bug #57151

  07 Jun 2004; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> xv-3.10a-r3.ebuild,
  xv-3.10a-r5.ebuild, xv-3.10a-r6.ebuild:
  Fix use invocation, fix sed expressions, add error checking

  17 Apr 2004; Travis Tilley <lv@gentoo.org> +files/xv-use-getcwd.patch,
  xv-3.10a-r6.ebuild:
  fix for segfaults on amd64

  17 Feb 2004; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> xv-3.10a-r6.ebuild:
  stable on alpha and ia64

  02 Feb 2004; Michael Sterrett <mr_bones_@gentoo.org> xv-3.10a-r3.ebuild,
  xv-3.10a-r5.ebuild, xv-3.10a-r6.ebuild:
  fix license for bug 17976

  19 Dec 2003; Guy Martin <gmsoft@gentoo.org> xv-3.10a-r6.ebuild:
  Marked stable on hppa.

  13 Nov 2003; <tuxus@gentoo.org> xv-3.10a-r6.ebuild:
  added mips to KEYWORDS

  06 Nov 2003; Mamoru KOMACHI <usata@gentoo.org> xv-3.10a-r3.ebuild,
  xv-3.10a-r5.ebuild, xv-3.10a-r6.ebuild:
  Changed to LIBDIR=/dev/null. xvdocs.ps was installed to /usr/lib
  (not a directory, but a file called /usr/lib !) due to absence of
  /usr/lib (we should dodir before calling make, if it is really
  necessary in the ebuild), but anyhow we dodoc xvdocs.ps in
  src_install so we don't need it.

